-- Nigeria in $600 Million Islamic Bank Loan Talks, ThisDay Says
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-02-10T08:22:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-10/nigeria-in-600-million-islamic-bank-loan-talks-thisday-says.html
Nigeria is in advanced talks to
secure a $600 million loan for infrastructure work from the
 Islamic Development Bank ,  ThisDay reported , citing Minister of
State for Finance Yerima Ngama.  The no-interest loan would be repaid in three to four
years, the Lagos-based newspaper reported Ngama saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Kay in Abuja at 
 ckay5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  